The internship will be carried out over a four-week period in the partner organisations ( e.g. Estonian
Government Office, Estonian Information System Authority, NATO StratCom Coe, Baltic Engagement
Center for Information Disorders that is part of the EDMO network and others) and supervised by the
university.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the traineeship is to put the theoretical and analytical knowledge into practice and gain
experience of working in organisations dealing with disinformation and strategic communication. Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course student - applies theoretical and analytical knowledge acquired during the studies and is able to solve
problems encountered in practical work; - applies the regulations, high ethical standards and best practices in the field when solving practical
problems; - creates an international supportive professional network for future work.
